New Records: Travis Head scored 137 runs off 120 balls, the fastest century in an ODI final since 1992.
Marnus Labuschagne scored 58 runs, remaining unbeaten
Key Match Events: Australia won the match by 6 wickets to secure the sixth ODI World Cup title
Pre-Game Insights: Australia were not favorites but ended up winning the World Cup title
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was Australia's second consecutive World Cup win after 2018-19
Others: The match was held at a slow pitch in Ahmedabad
